 The first step is to find a single female which, at the time of writing, (a) is not already married, (b) is relatively attractive, and (c) is of the species homo sapiens, (d) is not related to the individual at hand, and (e) is of a significantly different age. Once the specific female is identified, one must compose a marriage proposal and outwardly demonstrate interest in the female. The outward demonstration of interest involves establishing eye contact
